<br>
Am I out of luck? Can't this be done without some high level group taking out the Goblins first?<br>
<br>
I'm currently 34, and I had no problems with the other wands. I haven't tried LGuk yet, as that zone has always been deserted when I entered.. I was hoping to not have to wait till 39 when I get invis vs undead<br>
<br>
I'm not in a guild at the moment as I only get to play 1-2 weekends a month for the next half year <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tehutibloodstorm>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Blueberry Nuker</span><br>  Posts: 1365<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/26/03 7:43 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel</span><hr size=1> Stand on the very edge of the tower, and inch forward until you can pick up the rod piece. The tower is funny in that if you go on the floor of it you'll agro, but otherwise you're fine. Only some of the goblins see invis, not all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farekphirewalker>Farek Phirewalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/26/03 8:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the advice.<br>
Any particular direction which would be better to enter from? Paying for another corpse summoning isn't very tempting. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tehutibloodstorm>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Blueberry Nuker</span><br>  Posts: 1366<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/26/03 8:21 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel</span><hr size=1> Swim to the top of the tower, landing on it's edge. Con all the mobs to see which sees invis, work from there. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=manndrakke>Manndrakke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/26/03 10:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel</span><hr size=1> Lol Die twice , once picking the rod , twice picking the corpse. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-small;">One Wizard to rule them all, One Wizard to find them,<br>
