</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vaeles>Vaeles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/26/03 8:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Lake Rathe Rod</span><hr size=1> Okay, this was the only rod I died trying to retrieve, but I didn't die until after I picked up the rod, so I only had to retrieve my body.  Swim on the very top of the tunnel and just make a dive for the rod.  As soon as you grab it, one of the gobs will nail you and probably kill you, but you can go invis for a corpse run, swim out over the tower, and summon your corpse from there.  BTW, for those of you who are saving Guk for last, just bite the bullet and ask for help.  I found a lvl 52 pally to escort me and wipe out the hand room, otherwise, I would've been froggy dinner. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sarnath@graffeswizardcompilation>Sarnath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/27/03 12:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lake Rathe Rod</span><hr size=1> Another helpful thing for the Lake Rathe spoke is to get Shared Wolf Form from a Druid friend. The goblins won't aggro on you in Wolf Form - at least, they didn't aggro me, and I wasn't invisible. <br>
<br>
It's not exactly &quot;soloing&quot; by doing this, but it does work. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=foldarnmanabern>FoldarnManabern</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/28/03 9:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lake Rathe Rod</span><hr size=1> Aye.  Use wolf form there and you will be ok.  The only one I died from was Everfrost.  I drown and then I tried to solo the 3 skeles.  At that time they owned me even green. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=farekphirewalker>Farek Phirewalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/30/03 9:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lake Rathe Rod</span><hr size=1> The skellies went quickly down for me... blasted 'em with Ice Shock, and threw in a Shock of Lightning to finish them off. I was lucky to avoid Miragul tho, as some guy had been slaughtered near the water while I was with the skellies <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Thanks for the advices. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wokrred>Wokrred</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/2/03 10:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> This rod is a pain</span><hr size=1> Ya the shammy near the floor is what was killing me all the time when I did the quest, think I died 6 times getting this sucker.<br>
<br>
I quickly learned after the 2nd try to get the corpse with my gear and leave it on the surface until I was done getting this rod.<br>
<br>
Belive I was lvl 34 when I did the quest<br>
<br>
I learned from trial and error that you just need to stay about midway/near the top of the water to avoid aggro<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dayakdaemonspawn>Dayak Daemonspawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/9/03 5:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the wheel</span><hr size=1> I did this whole quest at lvl 21, just used invis to get all the peices except the guk one.<br>
<br>
In Lake Rathe, i just swam through one of the sides and picked up the staff as i swam by, didnt even stop.  Dont konw if i was lucky or what, but got no agro and made it out safely.<br>
<br>
In guk, a 52 Pally IvUed me and led me to hand room, hand was dead, picked up staff and gated out.  <br>
<br>
Was done and went to do trade in. <p>DAYAK DAEMONSPAWN<br>
<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm57.showPrevMessage?topicID=152.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm57.showNextMessage?topicID=152.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm57.emailToFriend?topicID=152.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm57.threadControl?topicID=152.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm57.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=152.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm57.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=152.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub140.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm60">Graffe Forum News<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General EQ Discussion<op